net.sf.jclec.algorithm.multiobjective

Class NSGA2

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.AbstractAlgorithm
      • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.PopulationAlgorithm
        • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.multiobjective.NSGA2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IAlgorithm, IConfigure, IPopulation, ISystem, JCLEC, IRandGenFactory

    public class NSGA2
extends PopulationAlgorithm
    "NSGA-II" algorithm. NSGA-II (Non-dominating Sorting Genetic Algorithm) is a multi-objective genetic optimization algorithm based on Pareto-optimal front with low computational requirements. It is an elitism algorithm. The main feature of NSGA2 is in elitism-preservation operation. Firstly, the archive size is set equal to the initial population size. The current archive is then determined based on the combination of the current population and the previous archive. To do this, NSGA2 uses dominance ranking to classify the population into a number of layers, and a truncation operator is applied to that layer based on crowding distance.
    Author:
    Amelia Zafra, Revised by: Jose Maria Luna, Alberto Cano
